How do I get the current command that is running on a subsystem, instead of always getting Sequential Command or Conditional Command, which are correct but not helpful? I am trying to display the current command on smartdashboard, but I am not sure how.

Currently I have tried:
SmartDashboard.putData(drive);
SmartDashboard.putString(“Drive”, drive.getCurrentCommand() == null ? “” : drive.getCurrentCommand().getName());

The goal is to see which particular command in a sequence, or which of the conditionals, etc, is running.

THANK YOU!

SequentialCommandGroup.initSendable adds an integer property representing the index of the current subcommand. I think, if you call putData with the command instead of calling putString on the name, then it should report that on whatever dashboard you’re using. Similarly, ConditionalCommand.initSendable has code to add the name of the selected subcommand as a string property.

Also, if you’re using nested command groups (or multiple instances of your own commands), remember that you can add withName() when creating instances to give them a distinguishable name.
